      "summary": "The **hantu bungkus** (literally \\\"wrapped ghost\\\" in Malay) is the restless spirit of a deceased person whose soul remains trapped within their white Islamic burial shroud (kain kafan).",
      "full": "The **hantu bungkus** (literally \\\"wrapped ghost\\\" in Malay) is the restless spirit of a deceased person whose soul remains trapped within their white Islamic burial shroud (kain kafan). This ghost represents one of the most distinctive elements of Malaysian Islamic folklore, serving both as a source of fear and as an important reminder of the proper respect owed to the dead and the crucial importance of correct burial procedures."
